## Content Architecture (Separation of Concerns)

**Pattern**: Separate content (data) from presentation (UI)

- **`pages/`**: Streamlit page files - handle UI rendering only
- **`src/content/`**: Content modules - store structured content using dataclasses
- **`src/data_loader.py`**: Defines dataclasses (`Subdomain`, `Reading`, `PracticeTask`, etc.)

**Rules for Content Files:**
- Store section content in `src/content/` modules (e.g., `domain_1.py`, `domain_2.py`)
- Use dataclasses from `src/data_loader.py` for type-safe content structures
- Export constants (e.g., `DOMAIN_1_SUBDOMAINS`, `DOMAIN_1_PRACTICE_TASKS`)
- Page files import content and render it - no hardcoded content in page files

**Example Structure:**
```python
# src/content/domain_1.py
from src.data_loader import Subdomain, PracticeTask, Reading

DOMAIN_1_SUBDOMAINS = [
    Subdomain(
        title="1. Principles, Features & Best Practices",
        objectives="...",
        readings=[Reading("Title", "URL"), ...]
    ),
    ...
]

DOMAIN_1_PRACTICE_TASKS = [
    PracticeTask(description="...", url="..."),
    ...
]
```

